				\begin{document}$R_{e}$\end{document}Re is defined as the number of secondary infections produced by a single infectious individual when the population has both susceptible and non-susceptible individuals (non-susceptible may include infectious, immune, vaccinated, etc.) and/or control methods have been implemented. Several previous studies have estimated \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
